    "content": "**CONFIRM.** Context-dependent is correct here. \"Nothingness\" works when the author is discussing the *condition* (虚无主义 as a state of meaning-loss). \"The void\" works when the author is using the spatial/cosmological metaphor (虚空, the emptiness left behind). Both appear in the text. Forcing one default would flatten a real distinction the author makes. The hard rule — never \"emptiness\" — is the important constraint, and that is already settled."
